STYLING FREEZE — non-negotiable (see REMEDIATION-PLAN.md, enforced by `npm run guardrails`):
1. NEVER create a new .css file. Style with Tailwind utility classes and the components in src/components/ui/.
2. NEVER add `!important`. If a style doesn't apply, fix the selector/cascade or migrate the element to Tailwind.
3. NEVER add a new `import "*.css"` in a .ts/.tsx file.
4. NEVER hardcode hex colors in components — use the design tokens in tailwind.config.ts / CSS variables.
5. NEVER add a new color namespace to tailwind.config.ts.
6. Before styling anything, check REMEDIATION-PLAN.md Phase 2 for the canonical component to use (one nav, one footer, one hero, one card, one button, one table).

Existing global stylesheets in src/app/*.css are legacy: they may only shrink or be deleted, never grow. After reducing CSS/!important, run `npm run guardrails:update` and commit the baseline.

For visual identity (colors, typography, spacing) consult DESIGN_SPEC.md, but note the codebase now has day+night themes; the "dark backgrounds only" rule in that spec is superseded.
